# CC PROMPT — v2.34.12 — feat(tools): container-introspection read-only tools

## Evidence

Live trace 2026-04-17 20:08 (session 2bd88acb). v2.34.11 classifier fix shipped
and working: agent correctly routed to Investigate with 16-call budget. Ran
the Logstash→ES investigation and made real progress, getting as far as the
in-container probe we need to diagnose overlay-layer Kafka reachability.

Of the 16 tool calls made, **5 of them were `docker exec ...` shapes that
the vm_exec allowlist blocked or filtered**:

| Step | Command | Outcome |
|---|---|---|
| 11 | `docker exec <logstash> nc -zv 192.168.199.33 9094` | Ran — but `nc` not installed in Logstash container |
| 12 | `docker exec <logstash> curl -I http://localhost:9094` | BLOCKED (segment not in allowlist) |
| 13 | `docker exec <logstash> cat /etc/resolv.conf` | BLOCKED |
| 14 | `docker exec <logstash> cat /etc/hosts` | BLOCKED |
| 15 | `docker exec <logstash> cat /opt/logstash/config/logstash.yml` | BLOCKED |

The agent then hit the token cap (123k > 120k) and was forced to escalate
without reaching a diagnosis. Manual follow-up in the chat established the
root cause — Logstash's overlay network has working cross-host routing to
brokers 1 and 2 but NOT to broker 3 on the same host (Docker hairpin-NAT
failure on worker-03). That diagnosis hinged on four facts the agent could
not obtain through `vm_exec` alone:

1. Logstash's `bootstrap_servers` config — needs `cat <config>` in container
2. Broker 3's advertised listeners — needs `env | grep ADVERTISED` in container
3. The overlay networks each container belongs to — needs `docker inspect`
   with a field-format filter
4. Whether Logstash can reach the broker port from **inside its netns** —
   needs `</dev/tcp/...>` probe in container (nc not installed)

Each of those is a safe, read-only operation that the existing vm_exec
allowlist cannot express without allowing broadly destructive `docker exec`
and `docker inspect` patterns. Dedicated tools with typed, constrained
arguments are the right safety boundary.

Version bump: 2.34.11 → 2.34.12 (new subsystem but small footprint —
five new tools in one file, one allowlist group, minor prompt additions).

